        },
        "subject": "LU-1030 osc: support to change max_pages_per_rpc",
        "message": "LU-1030 osc: support to change max_pages_per_rpc\n\nChanging max_pages_per_rpc is not easy as before any more after\nosc_extent is used because each extent relies on that value to make\nthe boundary correctly.\n\nIn this patch, when changing max_pages_per_rpc, it's allowed for\n`old' extents and `new' extents to co-exist for a short while, and\nthe greater one will be used to compose RPCs.\n\nSigned-off-by: Jinshan Xiong <jinshan.xiong@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ic157e9c9c117fb4ec029c2edfbc5021b5e993f47\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
